Operatives of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, Zamfara State Command have arrested three suspected vandals of armoured cables worth N205,000 (Two hundred and five thousand Naira), from Maru Local Government Area of the State. Parading the suspects before newsmen at the State Command headquarters in Gusau, the State Commandant of the Corps, Mr. A A Sparks, who spoke through the Command CDPRO said that the criminals had severally tampered with installations belonging to Kaduna Electricity Company, thereby depriving the general public the services of electricity in the Local Government Area. “And as such, the Corps will not relent in hunting down these kind of criminals who are hell-bent on truncating and sabotaging the candid efforts of the Government. “The suspects, who include Jamilu Mohd 18, Shehu Bashar 18 and Bashir Samaila 22, all confessed to the crime,” he said. According to the commandant, two other suspects, who were charged with criminal conspiracy and cheating were also arrested. He said that they were arrested for duplication of fake currency by the operatives of the Corps at Gusau metropolis. “One Summaya Bara, 35 years, female, conspired with one Mukhtar Musa, 52 years, to make fake currency for her and she eventually allegedly gave Mukhtar the sum of five hundred thousand Naira (N500000.00) to use for the duplication, to the sum of 3 million naira, via voodoo. “However, the said deal of duplication failed and the money given couldn’t be recovered by Summayya Bara. “The duo confessed to the crime of money doubling as Mukhtar accepted that he has been engaging in such act since 1999. “Exhibit recovered from Mukhtar include assorted spiritual perfumes, two white plane cloths,
four papers in the form of booklets, with ambiguous Arabic symbols used for voodoo,” he added. The state Commandant said that the suspects will be charged to a court of competent jurisdiction to face the law after the conclusion of investigations.